task.summary: properties declaration, hasProps type checker VVector - vector managing objects of arbitrary types via pointers Call - compile time type-conditional caller ManagerSingletons - contains single instance of each type TypeInfoManager - dynamic type info VariantCaller - calls correctly typed variant into functor
custom assert (with message & non-crashing) + minor changes
added Timer class added emscripten build
fixed bug with incorrectly setting redirect id when deleting item from unsortedvector getBase() for casting to currently set variant's bases + minor changes

VVector can be templated with types from typesPack also has addAs for specifying pointer type that is stored in vector macros for creating enums and extending enums convenience getter for typeInfo in typesPack

UnsortedVector removed instead added Array & TightArray (with holes) - has Pool & TightPool (internal struct for Array & TightArray)
Added SharedBuffer - refcounted buffer Added RoundBuffer hash funcs added to common.h Measure & BlockMeasure for debug time measurement & logging
Added SortedSet fast_vector rewrite: - cleaned - instead of mStart, mAllocEnd, mEnd now uses mStart, mSize, mCapacity - also probably a little faster
fixes for MultiPool defConstruction for MultiPool

added shorted typedefs for basic types enum macros now also define masks fixed warnings removed SimpleSet added Mask Clock inner implementation changed from std::chrono to windows specific (QueryPerformanceTimer ...) (TODO: do for linux), because chrono has shitty precision & performance
